properties.Name: PremiumPaymentPeriod
properties.Description:
The period or mode under which policyholders may pay their premiums.

- Annually
- Semi-annually
- Quarterly
- Monthly

On any policy anniversary date if company rules allow, the Policyholder typically can change the payment period.

All premiums are normally payable in advance.

There is a slight extra charge normally for premiums that are not paid annually.

Columns.Name: PremiumPaymentPeriodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Premium Payment Period.

Columns.Description: The name of a Premium Payment Period.
